## Linking rules

| From | To sibling in same lesson | To another lesson | To images |
|------|---------------------------|-------------------|-----------|
| `docs/index.md` | — | `lesson-NN/<file>.md` | `images/...` |
| `docs/lesson-NN/*.md` | `plain-language.md`, `quiz.md`, etc. | `../lesson-MM/<file>.md` | `../images/...` |

## Navigation — always keep in sync

When adding or renaming a doc, update **both**:

1. `mkdocs.yml` → `nav:` section (under the correct module tab + lesson group)
2. `docs/index.md` → Modules table and/or Practice table

Nav is grouped by course module (Foundations, Routing, Router Design, SDN, Security, Applications) with sticky header tabs. Each lesson uses Guide / Plain-language / Quick study / Quiz child labels. See **mkdocs-theme** rule for feature flags and CSS conventions.

## Non-negotiables

- **Accuracy first** — content reflects CS 6250 / Kurose & Ross course material, not generic blog posts.
- **Relative links** — sibling links use short names; cross-lesson links use `../lesson-NN/...`.
- **Local images** — `../images/descriptive-name.png` from lesson folders.
- **No new doc types** — do not invent README files, CHANGELOGs, or extra markdown the user did not ask for.
- **MkDocs Material syntax** — admonitions (`!!! tip`), collapsible answers (`??? success`), tables, mermaid, MathJax `$...$`.

## Cross-linking between formats

Every lesson variant should link siblings near the top. Follow `docs/lesson-01/introduction.md` (exam-prep admonition) or `docs/lesson-03/plain-language.md` (intro paragraph).

Lesson 3 ↔ Lesson 4 cross-link explicitly at the IGP/BGP handoff.
